f'(x) &= \underbrace{x\ddx e^x + e^x \ddx x }_{\text{Product Rule}} \\ &= x\cdot e^x + e^x = \dfx \end{align} %text Now, $e^x \neq 0$ for all values of $x$. Hence, \[ \qquad\qquad f'(x) = 0 \implies x = -1 \] %

